Ι. 2. 1 n.). It was from the assumption of the tribunician power that the emperors dated their reigns. The association of Agrippa and Tiberius in this office was equivalent to nominating them as successors, and that was the mean- ing of the present association of Drusus (ne successor in incerto foret).
